cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a novel method for training robust CNNs for this task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning and metric learning techniques, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on several benchmarks, which suggests that it may also be relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
